commit.message:
data: Update appdata location, format and content

According to https://www.freedesktop.org/software/appstream/docs/chap-Metadata.html ,
we should not install appdata to /usr/share/appdata anymore.
Besides, the appdata file format is updated as well.

The broken homepage information in appdata xml is also fixed.

commit.message:
Properly import gi modules to avoid PyGIWarning

Fix #86

Merge pull request #79 from yookoala/docker

Docker based test

Update travis config to contributors comment

* moved `services` section after `env` to match order of other
  projects in Cangjians stack.

* use `before_install` instead of `install` for docker image
  installation to match other projects in Cangjains stack.

* remove `sudo` in docker statements.

* use long options `--tag` instead of `-t` in docker build command.

* remove unnecessary `-lt` options.

Added various status shield to README.md

* Added title in README.md for readability.
* Added travis build status shield.
* Added license shield for visibility of license.

Only run Travis CI for master branch

* prevent duplication when doing pull request.

Implement Dockerhub build hook

* Build image with OS tag name from DOCKER_TAG.

Adopt the new image tags in Dockerhub

* use the new image tags to identify the OS specific images.

Pretty print the OS name in travis's docker

* ensure that the test is running on the correct image.

Don't run both check and distcheck

* Only run distcheck.

Simplified Travis file to only run docker test

* Remove local test scripts.
* Remove local docker image build scripts and adopt OS-specific
  docker image of pycangjie directly from Dockerhub.

Adopt new Dockerfile format

* Use ARG `OS` to inject image tag for pycangjie instead of
  hardcode to "latest".

* Remove unnecessary ENTRYPOINT and CMD statement (because
  we have no long running process.
Travis: Add opensuse-leap as test target

travis: Test docker build

Test Dockerfile build in travis.

Fix #78.

Basic docker setup

Added Dockerfile and .dockerignore for building the docker image
"cangjians/ibus-cangjie" from "cangjians/pycangjie".

This image is an essential ground for testing ibus-cangjie and / or
other software based upon libcangjie in docker environment.

Merge pull request #70 from Cangjians/release-2.4

Release 2.4
Release 2.4

Work around the candidate popup position issue

Some applications (most notably Firefox) fail to correctly position the
candidate popup.

This is because we don't use a pre-edit text at all, and it seems those
applications (or maybe the toolkits?) get confused by the absence of a
pre-edit text. :(

This is a gross hack. The real issue needs to be fixed in the
apps/toolkits, but we need to do something in the meantime, as this is
just too much of a bad UX issue for us.

The idea comes from FrÃdÃric Péter.

Fixes #60

Merge pull request #68 from Cangjians/setup-tb

setup: Don't traceback when the halfwidth-chars property changes

setup: Don't traceback when the halfwidth-chars property changes

The issue would only happen if a user changed the property while the
setup dialog was opened.

It doesn't crash the dialog, it just sends a traceback, but it is still
pretty ugly as it can get caught by crash-reporting systems like ABRT or
Apport.
